# Astro Conventions

## Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.astro` (e.g. `HeroSection.astro`).
- Split files: same base name + suffix:
  - `HeroSection.styles.astro`
  - `HeroSection.scripts.astro`
- Content modules: `kebab-case.ts` or feature name (`hero.ts`, `toolbar.ts`) under `src/assets/contents/`.
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` (`SOCIAL_LINKS`, `HERO_CONTENT`).
- CSS classes: `kebab-case`, BEM-style blocks for complex UI (`popup-modal__panel`).

## When to split styles/scripts

- **≤10 lines:** keep inline in the main `.astro` file.
- **>10 lines:** extract to `.styles.astro` / `.scripts.astro` and import as components.
- Critical init scripts (e.g. theme flash prevention) may stay as `is:inline` in `Layout.astro` `<head>`.

## i18n

- Routes: `/en/...`, `/fa/...`; `lang` param type from `src/i18n/config.ts`.
- `Layout` receives `locale`; pass `lang` to sections and `getContent()` bundles.

## Do not

- Inline locale strings in `.astro` templates.
- Use raw `<a>` where `Link` / `SocialLink` / `Button` applies.
- Scope styles in a split file that only apply to elements rendered by a different component.
